body:
Prevents the following solution from being correct:

``` javascript
function mutation(arr) {
  var foo = arr[0].toLowerCase().split('').sort();
  var bar = arr[1].toLowerCase().split('').sort();
  var start = foo.indexOf(bar[0]);

  for(var i = 0; i < bar.length; i++)
    if(foo[start + i] !== bar[i]) return false;

  return true;
}
```

Users searching for just occurrence of target and not the position(in this case the ending of the string) in this bonfire can pass the tests. So , currently this code pass the tests

```
function end(str, target) {
  return str.split(target) != str;
}
```

Added tests to fix this flaw.

This adds more test cases to the 'Convert HTML Entities'-bonfire. The new test cases now checks for all the characters instead of just '&', and they also check that mutlitple characters in a string is converted, preventing solutions which would only convert the first character, like this one:

``` javascript
function converter(m) {
    switch(m) {
        case '&':
            return "&amp;";
        case '<':
            return "&lt;";
        case '>':
            return "&gt;";
        case '"':
            return "&quot;";
        case "'":
            return "&apos;";
    }
}

function convert(str) {
    return str.replace(/([&<>"'])/, converter);
}
```

- Removed stamps so code stays stored until code has been reset. 
- Added a feature which returns if the storage has been saved since last edit. `codeStorage.hasSaved();` 
- Changed "localBonfire" to _codeStorage_

**New Save Listener:**

```
codeStorage.onSave(function(){
    console.log("editor has been saved!");
    $("#save-notifier").empty().text("last save..."+Date);
});
```

-**Less dependencies**: `codeStorage.setSaveKey("unique id");` 
setSaveKey takes away the dependency the object had relying on the variable: challenge_Name
